<item>
            <title>[LU-298] autoconf dpkg test needs improvment</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-298</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I was going to point out that the dpkg test should be improved to through away stderr.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, it now occurs to me that this test should be changed further.  Assuming that an rpm system will not have the dpkg binary, or that a deb system will not have the rpm binary is not the best assumption.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Our RHEL6 clusters do in fact have dpkg, and I know I have the rpm command installed on my Ubuntu box.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A better test would probably check the OS distributor ID or somesuch.  For instance:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;$ lsb_release -i -s&lt;br/&gt;
Ubuntu&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On a Debian system, the response is &quot;Debian&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll submit a patch.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
                <environment>RHEL6</environment>
